      <aside class="calc-sidebar">
        <div class="card sidebar-card">
          <h2>What is a proportion?</h2>
          <p>A proportion is an equation stating that two ratios are equal. The rule of three (or cross-multiplication method) is a technique to find an unknown value in a proportion when three values are known.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card sidebar-card">
          <h3>Frequently asked questions</h3>
          <details>
            <summary>What is the difference between direct and inverse proportion?</summary>
            <p>In direct proportion both quantities change in the same direction — if one doubles, the other doubles too. In inverse proportion they change in opposite directions — if one doubles, the other halves.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>How do I know if a proportion is direct or inverse?</summary>
            <p>Ask: if A increases, does B increase or decrease? If increase → direct. If decrease → inverse. Example: more speed, less time → inverse.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>What is cross-multiplication?</summary>
            <p>For direct proportion: X = (B × C) ÷ A. For inverse proportion: X = (A × B) ÷ C. This calculator applies the correct formula automatically.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
